{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PLAN-REVIEW REMEDIATION (rounds 2-4) + claim. Round-1 BLOCK (G6 threshold mechanism): resolved by aligning to the SHIPPED plan-review precedent — thresholds live in a COMMITTED criteria_routing.json read by the registry's threshold_for, NOT in gates/code-review.yaml (WS3's file holds no threshold values). Round-2/3 BLOCKs: added a docs/review-kernel.md 'code-review consumer' section (captures the novel patterns); dropped the 'derived/regenerate-no-diff' overpromise (criteria_routing.json is hand-maintained + test-validated, matching the precedent); removed the false 'WS3's EXISTING overlay_triggers op already reads these globs' claim (the Round-A glob-match trigger LOGIC is WS3's work; WS2 supplies only the glob DATA in criteria_routing.json, single-sourced — not duplicated in front-matter). Round-4 -> VERDICT PASS, 0 blocking, signed.\n\nResidual 9 advisories (all non-blocking; baked into implementation or acknowledged):\n- A2 (active_triggers): defined as the union of criteria across surviving findings (matches plan-review's pass4_coach); implemented as such.\n- A6 (verify re-grounds against diff = measurable): a test asserts code-review-verify.md embeds VERIFIER_RULES_SCAFFOLD verbatim + references the diff context var.\n- A7 (exact prompt ids): the overlay prompts are code-review-<overlay_id> (e.g. code-review-security); resolve via get_prompt.\n- A8 (coach pick failure): kernel coach() returns [] on empty picks; gate-level recovery is WS3's (mirrors plan-review). A9 (separate coach prompt): warranted — code moves + code active_triggers differ from plan moves.\n- A1/A3/A5/A4 (routing-index duplication concern, glob calibration deferred, file count/thin-slice, AC phrasing): acknowledged; structural-floor nitpicks left intentionally."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782821261645369001,"uuid":"3610dd56-b86c-4e62-bce8-3c09b0e3c42b"}